                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="legend-note-text" value="&lt;i style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Both flows are structurally identical. Key differences from standard order flow:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Only direct recipients are supported (phone number / email address) —&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(63, 63, 63);&quot;&gt;no NIN, org number, or Profile API lookup&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;Notifications are dispatched via a synchronous HTTP call, not via ASB queue&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;A single NotificationOrder is persisted (no chain / reminders).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(63, 63, 63);&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: rgb(63, 63, 63);&quot;&gt;Delivery reports are still received asynchronously.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fontSize=10;align=left;spacingLeft=5;spacingRight=5;strokeColor=none;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="384" y="1250" width="412" height="140" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
